# Netlify _redirects — SPA fallback.
# Flutter web uses PathUrlStrategy (path-based URLs, no # prefix). The
# catch-all rewrites any unknown path to index.html with a 200 so GoRouter
# takes over client-side. Required for deep-link and hard-refresh support.
#
# Static files (assets/, icons/, canvaskit/, *.js, *.json, *.png, etc.) are
# served as files because Netlify checks the literal path before applying
# the rewrite — only paths that don't match a real file fall through here.
#
# Smart front door: the bare root serves the static marketing page
# (welcome.html), which detects an existing EQ session client-side and bounces
# returning/core users straight to /splash — so only cold visitors see the
# pitch. This exact-match rule MUST come before the SPA catch-all (first match
# wins). Every other path still falls through to the Flutter app, so deep links
# (/claim, /join, /email, …) and the live pilot are unaffected.
# NOTE: _redirects is the authoritative source — the deploy zips build/web only,
# so the repo-root netlify.toml is not shipped. Keep this rule here.

/             /welcome.html   200
/*            /index.html     200
